## üöÄ How to Manage Content (FireCMS)

Since we now have the data in Firestore, you can set up **FireCMS** to manage it visually.

### Option 1: FireCMS Cloud (Easiest)
1. Go to [app.firecms.co](https://app.firecms.co).
2. Create an account and **New Project**.
3. Connect your Firebase Project (`app-learn-english-flutter`).
4. You will see your `topics` collection immediately!

### Option 2: Self-hosted (Ready!)
I have already set up a local FireCMS project for you in the `admin` folder.

#### To start the Admin Panel:
1. Open a new terminal.
2. Navigate to the admin folder: `cd admin`
3. Start the server: `npm run dev`
4. Open the link (usually http://localhost:5173).
5. Log in with Google (ensure your account has access to the Firebase project).

You can now edit Topics and Vocabularies visually! Changes will sync to the app immediately.

